"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-blitzboks-star-journey-from-darkness-to-bronze-was-special\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 63, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999999797173589, \"rank\": 2.028245180333427e-08, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbBlitzboks star: The journey from 'darkness' to 'bronze' was special  Rosko Specman has written his name into Springbok Sevens history after becoming the first Blitzbok to win two Olympic medals.\", \"from\": 65, \"to\": 398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 107, \"end\": 110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999999797173589, \"rank\": 2.028245180333427e-08, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 273, \"end\": 278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rosko\", \"score\": 0.9999999993219717, \"rank\": 5.405199483502685e-10, \"text\": \"Rosko\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rosko\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rosko\"}, {\"begin\": 279, \"end\": 286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Specman\", \"score\": 0.8020135056823948, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Specman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Specman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Specman\"}, {\"begin\": 313, \"end\": 329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Springbok Sevens\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite once being in real danger of missing out on Olympic qualification, the Blitzboks ultimately achieved a second podium finish in three Summer Games, having claimed the bronze medal on Saturday.\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 479, \"end\": 488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Blitzboks\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the Blitzboks suffered an agonising defeat to France in the semi-finals, the SA teambounced back to beat Australia for the bronze medalat the Stade de France.\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 653, \"end\": 659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999716851566, \"rank\": 2.785336487804604e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 684, \"end\": 686, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1020192962085437e-24, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 712, \"end\": 721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 2.9817804166872485e-12, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 749, \"end\": 764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rosko Specman, who became the first rugby player to earn two medals at the Olympics, said the second meant as much as the first achieved in Rio in 2016.\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 919, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 767, \"end\": 772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rosko\", \"score\": 0.9999999993219717, \"rank\": 5.405199483502685e-10, \"text\": \"Rosko\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rosko\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rosko\"}, {\"begin\": 773, \"end\": 780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Specman\", \"score\": 0.8020135056823948, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Specman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Specman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Specman\"}, {\"begin\": 907, \"end\": 910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 5.53651194304812e-12, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What a journey it has been for me, to earn two medals eight years apart - that is special,\\\" said Specman.\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 1027, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1019, \"end\": 1026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Specman\", \"score\": 0.8020135056823948, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Specman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Specman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Specman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But even more special is the journey we had to get to this point.\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1095, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From the dark moments in Harare, where we missed out on qualification, to Monaco, where we used our final chance.\", \"from\": 1096, \"to\": 1209, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1121, \"end\": 1127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harare\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4014429926888912e-13, \"text\": \"Harare\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harare\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harare\"}, {\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monaco\", \"score\": 0.7569070350402994, \"rank\": 0.3211606086380602, \"text\": \"Monaco\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monaco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monaco\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We may have been the last team in, but we are bronze medallists.\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1276, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Well done to the coaches and management who got this group to believe it is possible.\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1362, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And on a personal note, I would like to thank God who gave me this chance to earn a second medal in the Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1477, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Philip Snyman, a member of the 2016 squad that won a medal in the inaugural Rugby Sevens event, achieving a second - this time as coach - said it was more important that the credit should go to the players who made it possible, rather than his own achievement.\", \"from\": 1479, \"to\": 1739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1479, \"end\": 1492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Snyman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philip Snyman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Snyman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Snyman\"}, {\"begin\": 1555, \"end\": 1567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rugby_sevens\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.9915502502023255e-13, \"text\": \"Rugby Sevens\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rugby_sevens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rugby_sevens\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have a great management, and this win was also for those back in South Africa, but the moment belongs to the players - I am so proud of them and what they achieved here today,\\\" said Snyman.\", \"from\": 1741, \"to\": 1934, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1810, \"end\": 1822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"score\": 0.9999991080362064, \"rank\": 7.786787877235028e-07, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We had our ups and downs, especially on the first day, but the way the team came back on the next two competition days made me so proud.\", \"from\": 1936, \"to\": 2073, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We had our lapses and could have been in the final, but all that matters will be the bronze medals they earned today.\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2193, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is so deserved to a group of guys who never stopped working and playing for their country.\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We were gutted after the France defeat, but the players showed huge courage to come out and fight for that bronze medal against Australia.\", \"from\": 2289, \"to\": 2428, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2315, \"end\": 2321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999716851566, \"rank\": 2.785336487804604e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2418, \"end\": 2427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 2.9817804166872485e-12, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am so proud of them, as I am sure South Africa will be for their first medal at the Paris Games.\\\"\", \"from\": 2429, \"to\": 2528, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2465, \"end\": 2477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"score\": 0.9999991080362064, \"rank\": 7.786787877235028e-07, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's Team South Africa'sschedule for Monday(29 July):  11am: Equestrian (Eventing, individual jumping) - Alexander Peternell  (Finals will follow at 3pm if Peternell progresses)  12pm: Skateboarding (Men's Street) - Brandon Valjalo  (Men's Street finals will follow at 5pm if Valjalo progresses)  2pm: Badminton (Women's Singles) - Johanita Scholtz (SA) vs Goh Jin Wei (Malaysia)  2pm: Rugby Sevens (Women's) - South Africa vs Great Britain  (Quarterfinals will follow at 8pm if SA progresses)  2:10pm: Mountain Biking (Men's Cross-Country) - Alan Hatherly  5:30pm: Hockey (Women's) - South Africa vs Argentina  7pm: Surfing (Men's) - Jordy Smith (SA) vs Alonso Correa (Peru)  9:19pm: Swimmin